This paper deals with knowledge representation and reasoning, which is a core topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a new probabilistic description logic, which falls under the category of mathematical logic (cs.LO). The use of maximum entropy principle for probabilistic reasoning suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses reasoning algorithms and logical dependencies, which are relevant to database systems (cs.DB). Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing and semantics, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
